1 olive oil
1 packet Beef Rump
½ tin sweetcorn
1 cucumber
1 tomato
1 bag salad leaves
½ lemon
1 packet Mild Chipotle Sauce
1 packet sour cream
1 bag slaw mix
1 packet Corn Chips
1 bag herbs
1 sachet Tex-Mex spice blend

• Place beef between two sheets of
baking paper. Pound with rolling pin
until slightly flattened (this ensures
it’s extra tender!)
• In a bowl, combine beef and spice
blend with a drizzle of olive oil.
Season
• Heat oil in a frying pan over high heat
• Cook beef, turning, for 5-6 mins or
until cooked to your liking
• Transfer to a plate

• Drain corn
• Roughly chop cucumber, tomato
and salad leaves. Slice lemon into
wedges
• In a bowl, combine corn, cucumber,
tomato, salad leaves, slaw mix,
1/2 the chipotle sauce, 1/2 the sour
cream, a squeeze of lemon juice and
a drizzle of olive oil. Season

• Slice steak
• In a bowl, combine remaining
chipotle sauce and sour cream
• Plate up slaw and steak
• Serve with corn chips, torn herbs,
chipotle sour cream and any
remaining lemon wedges